#: en/gimp-using-variable-size-brush.html:86(p)
msgid "By programming the mouse wheel:"
msgstr ""

#: en/gimp-using-variable-size-brush.html:89(p)
msgid "In the main window of GIMP, click on <span class=\"guimenu\">Edit</span> → <span class=\"guimenuitem\">Preferences</span>."
msgstr ""

#: en/gimp-using-variable-size-brush.html:95(p)
msgid "In the left column of the new window, select <span class=\"guimenu\">Input Devices</span> → <span class=\"guimenuitem\">Input Controllers</span>."
msgstr ""

#: en/gimp-using-variable-size-brush.html:101(p)
msgid "You can see <span class=\"guibutton\">Additional Input Controllers</span>, with two columns: <span class=\"guibutton\">Available Controllers</span> and <span class=\"guibutton\">Active Controllers</span>."
msgstr ""

#: en/gimp-using-variable-size-brush.html:108(p)
msgid "In the column <span class=\"guibutton\">Active Controllers</span>, double-click the <span class=\"guibutton\">Main Mouse Wheel</span> button."
msgstr ""

#: en/gimp-using-variable-size-brush.html:115(p)
msgid "Then, you see a new window: <span class=\"guibutton\">Configure Input Controller</span>."
msgstr ""

#: en/gimp-using-variable-size-brush.html:119(p)
msgid "In the left column <span class=\"guibutton\">Event</span>, click <span class=\"guibutton\">Scroll Up</span> to get it highlighted."
msgstr ""

#: en/gimp-using-variable-size-brush.html:125(p)
msgid "Click the <span class=\"guibutton\">Edit</span> button (at the bottom middle of the list)."
msgstr ""

#: en/gimp-using-variable-size-brush.html:131(p)
msgid "You can see the window <span class=\"guibutton\">Select Controller Event Action</span>."
msgstr ""

#: en/gimp-using-variable-size-brush.html:135(p)
msgid "Drop-down the <span class=\"guibutton\">Tools</span> item, by clicking the small triangle on its left."
msgstr ""

#: en/gimp-using-variable-size-brush.html:142(p)
msgid "In the left column <span class=\"guibutton\">Action</span>, click <span class=\"guibutton\">Increase Brush Scale</span> to highlight it, then click the <span class=\"guibutton\">OK</span> button."
msgstr ""

#: en/gimp-using-variable-size-brush.html:149(p)
msgid "Now, in front of <span class=\"guibutton\">Scroll Up</span> is display <span class=\"guibutton\">tools-paint-brush-scale-increase</span>."
msgstr ""

#: en/gimp-using-variable-size-brush.html:156(p)
msgid "Close the window."
msgstr ""

#: en/gimp-using-variable-size-brush.html:161(p)
msgid "With the same method, program <span class=\"guibutton\">Scroll Down</span> with <span class=\"guibutton\">Decrease Brush Scale</span>."
msgstr ""

#: en/gimp-using-variable-size-brush.html:168(p)
msgid "Don't forget to click the <span class=\"guibutton\">OK</span> button of the main window of <span class=\"guibutton\">Preferences</span>."
msgstr ""

#: en/gimp-using-variable-size-brush.html:176(p)
msgid "After these somewhat long explanations, you can use your mouse wheel to vary size brush. For example, choose the pencil tool with the “<span class=\"quote\">Circle</span>” brush. Set the pointer in the image window, use the mouse wheel, in the two directions, you can see the “<span class=\"quote\">Circle</span>” shrinking or stretching."
msgstr ""

#: en/gimp-using-variable-size-brush.html:186(p)
msgid "You can program the “<span class=\"quote\">Up</span>” and “<span class=\"quote\">Down</span>” arrow keys of the keyboard."
msgstr ""

#: en/gimp-using-variable-size-brush.html:190(p)
msgid "The method is similar to that of the mouse wheel. The only differences are:"
msgstr ""

#: en/gimp-using-variable-size-brush.html:197(p)
msgid "In the column <span class=\"guibutton\">Active Controllers</span>, double-click <span class=\"guibutton\">Main Keyboard</span>."
msgstr ""

#: en/gimp-using-variable-size-brush.html:204(p)
msgid "In the column <span class=\"guibutton\">Event</span>, click <span class=\"guibutton\">Cursor Up</span> for the first key, and <span class=\"guibutton\">Cursor Down</span> for the second key."
msgstr ""

#: en/gimp-using-variable-size-brush.html:211(p)
msgid "Then, use the two keys (Up arrow and Down arrow) and the result is the same as you got with the mouse wheel."
msgstr ""

